                            <hr />
            </article>

                                                                                
            
        
    <article class="art-hed">
        <h3><a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2019/12/beyond-the-arc-duke-mens-basketball-virginia-tech-joey-baker-jordan-goldwire-jack-white">Beyond the arc: Duke men&#039;s basketball&#039;s bench leads team to first win at Virginia Tech since 2015</a></h3>
                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>Notre Dame is by no means good without Colson, so it is difficult to draw any sort of meaningful conclusions from Monday's action. However, the Blue Devil defense has been trending up since getting torched by N.C. State Jan. 6.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The competition hasn't been tough—they haven't played a team ranked in the top six in the conference in scoring offense, but the intensity has been there. Duke's first real test on defense will come Feb. 8 against North Carolina in Chapel Hill.</p>
